  "text": "In vivo ubiquitinylation of the substrate was assayed after immunoprecipitation followed by immunoblotting with anti-myc antibody. Wild-type (WT) and sse1⌬ yeast cells transformed with copper-inducible myc-ubiquitin plasmid were grown to midlog phase (OD ϳ 0.8) in selective media in the presence of 0.1 mM CuSO 4 [CITATION_1] . Equal amounts of cells were divided in three parts and incubated with DMSO, GA (20 M), and MG132 (100 M) for 1 h. Cells were harvested and washed with cold water containing 4 mM N-ethylmaleimide (NEM) to inhibit deubiquitinylating enzymes. Cell extracts were prepared by resuspending the pellet in 150 l ice-cold extraction buffer (50 mM Tris, pH 7.5, 1 mM EDTA, 1% SDS, 8 M urea, 1 mM PMSF, 10 mM NEM, and 1ϫ protease inhibitor cocktail) followed by lysing in a bead beater at 4°C after adding an equal volume of glass beads. Extracts were clarified at 13, 000 ϫ g for 10 min. The supernatant, 100 l , was diluted 10-fold with IP dilution buffer (60 mM Tris-HCl, pH 7.5, 190 mM NaCl, 1.25% Triton X-100, 6 mM EDTA, 1 mM PMSF, 10 mM NEM, and protease inhibitor cocktail). Monoclonal Anti-His antibody was added, and the samples were nutated overnight at 4°C. Immunoprecipitates were adsorbed onto protein A/G Sepharose (Pierce) resin for 2 h at 4°C and washed three times with IP wash buffer (10 mM Tris, pH 7.5, and 50 mM NaCl). The samples were boiled in 2ϫ urea-sample buffer (75 mM MOPS, pH 6.8, 8 M urea, 4% SDS, 0.2 M ␤-mercaptoethanol, and 0.2 mg/ml bromophenol blue) and resolved by SDS-PAGE.",
